{"content":"---\ntitle: \"Compiler Error CS0227\"\nms.date: 07/20/2015\nf1_keywords:\n  - \"CS0227\"\nhelpviewer_keywords:\n  - \"CS0227\"\nms.assetid: b595a1c9-8204-4ff7-a1d0-258b0b1d6ff7\n---\n# Compiler Error CS0227\n\nUnsafe code may only appear if compiling with /unsafe\n\nIf source code contains the [unsafe](../../csharp/language-reference/keywords/unsafe.md) keyword, then the [/unsafe](../../csharp/language-reference/compiler-options/unsafe-compiler-option.md) compiler option must also be used. For more information, see [Unsafe Code and Pointers](../../csharp/programming-guide/unsafe-code-pointers/index.md).\n\nTo set the unsafe option in Visual Studio 2012, click on **Project** in the main menu, select the **Build** pane, and check the box that says \"allow unsafe code.\"\n\nThe following sample, when compiled without **/unsafe**, generates CS0227:\n\n```csharp\n// CS0227.cs\npublic class MyClass\n{\n   unsafe public static void Main()   // CS0227\n   {\n   }\n}\n```\n\n## See also\n\n- [C# Compiler Errors](../../csharp/language-reference/compiler-messages/index.md)\n","nodes":[{"pos":[4,163],"embed":true,"restype":"x-metadata","content":"title: \"Compiler Error CS0227\"\nms.date: 07/20/2015\nf1_keywords:\n  - \"CS0227\"\nhelpviewer_keywords:\n  - \"CS0227\"\nms.assetid: b595a1c9-8204-4ff7-a1d0-258b0b1d6ff7","nodes":[{"content":"Compiler Error CS0227","nodes":[{"pos":[0,21],"content":"Compiler Error CS0227","nodes":[{"content":"Compiler Error CS0227","pos":[0,21]}]}],"path":["title"],"nosxs":false}],"yml":true},{"pos":[170,191],"content":"Compiler Error CS0227","linkify":"Compiler Error CS0227","nodes":[{"content":"Compiler Error CS0227","pos":[0,21]}]},{"content":"Unsafe code may only appear if compiling with /unsafe","pos":[193,246]},{"content":"If source code contains the <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>unsafe<ept id=\"p1\">](../../csharp/language-reference/keywords/unsafe.md)</ept> keyword, then the <bpt id=\"p2\">[</bpt>/unsafe<ept id=\"p2\">](../../csharp/langua